Al-Azhar calls on the international community to prosecute the Zionist entity and break the siege on the Gaza Strip
11/14/2023 at 02:06 AM Al-Thawra Net/Al-Akhbar

Al-Azhar Al-Sharif called on the international community to prosecute the Zionist entity that prevented fuel and medical supplies from hospitals in the Gaza Strip, calling on international institutions to take urgent action to break this “inhumane” siege imposed by the terrorist Zionists on Gaza’s hospitals. He stressed that silence on the crimes of the Israeli occupation is a "disgrace" on humanity and the international community.

He said in a tweet on his official account on the “X” platform: “Al-Azhar Al-Sharif calls on the international community to prosecute the terrorist Zionist entity that prevented fuel and medical supplies from hospitals, so intensive care patients and nursery children were martyred in Al-Shifa Hospital, and its insane bombing of the hospital’s surroundings caused the fall of dozens of martyrs.” Those whose burial was prohibited.”

He pointed out that the criminal, terrorist Zionist entity was devoid of all meanings of mercy and humanity, and displayed its tyranny against the sick, children, women, and the elderly, and committed the most heinous crimes that animals in the jungle would not pardon.

Al-Azhar Al-Sharif saluted the brave doctors of the Gaza Strip and its valiant medical staff, who led the front lines to rescue the wounded and heal the wounds of the injured, and who stood and fought on their own under the barbaric bombing of the terrorist entity and did not fear death, stressing that these heroes set an example in sacrifice and giving the precious and valuable.

He called on all the free people of the world to wash their hands of supporting this entity, which has demonstrated its cruelty and devoid of all meanings of mercy and humanity, shedding the blood of innocents, displaying its tyranny over the sick, children, women and the elderly, and committing the most heinous crimes that animals in the jungle are forgiving of.
